title: After laying off thousands, Meta expects to add jobs next year
description: The company said it’s poised to increase its hiring in technical roles for areas such as artificial intelligence and the metaverse.

title: AI researchers uncover ethical, legal risks to using popular data sets
description: The Data Provenance Initiative analyzed data sets used to build generative AI and found confusion surrounding licencing and fair use.

title: White House to unveil sweeping AI executive order next week, tackling immigration, safety
description: President Biden’s long-anticipated AI executive order marks the government’s most significant attempt to regulate the swiftly evolving technology.

title: Sam Bankman-Fried to testify at his fraud trial as it draws to a close
description: The founder of the now-defunct crypto exchange FTX will take the stand later this week after his inner circle testified against him, his lawyer said.

title: Apple is pushing repair laws but still puts limits on iPhone fixes
description: “Parts pairing” makes iPhones trickier for local, independent repair shops to fully fix, and repair advocates aren’t pleased.
